    {
      "id": "ch4-m02",
      "title": "The 7 social engineering principles",
      "tag_ids": [
        "se_authority",
        "se_intimidation",
        "se_social_proof",
        "se_scarcity",
        "se_familiarity",
        "se_trust",
        "se_urgency"
      ],
      "pages": [
        {
          "id": "ch4-m02-p01",
          "title": "The principles list",
          "content_blocks": [
            {
              "type": "explain",
              "text": "Most common principles:\n\n- **Authority**: “I’m your manager / government / IT admin.”\n- **Intimidation**: threats, bullying, fear.\n- **Consensus (social proof)**: “Everyone already did it.”\n- **Scarcity**: “Last chance / limited supply.”\n- **Familiarity**: you like the person/brand.\n- **Trust**: attacker builds relationship/credibility.\n- **Urgency**: “Do it NOW or bad things happen.”"
            }
          ],
          "checks": [
